</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636D2FFCEFFCFF7ECFCF4EF51FC2B" blockId="11.[2085,2669,442,860]" lastBlockId="11.[1468,2672,867,2040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="418">
In addition to its native range, introduced populations of this species are found on the islands of 
<collectingCountry id="F31E7642FFCEFFCFF708FCD4EF24FC7D" box="[2243,2329,867,900]" name="Guam" pageId="11" pageNumber="418">Guam</collectingCountry>
, Saipan and Rota in the Mariana Is and Pohnpei in the Caroline Is. The Philippine Brown Deer was also introduced to the Japanese Bonin Islands, where it later became extinct.
</paragraph>
</caption>
